er someone build a small ashram for hi=\r\nm. Totapuri&#39;s ashram still \nexists in Puri. In that conversation, Totapuri =\r\nalso mentions a similar ideas of \nwhat is a siddha and higher. And how only=\r\n a Siddha and none less is a true \nVigyani. He further mentions that Swami =\r\nVivekananda did not (need) to go to the \nstage of a Siddha. His work was sp=\r\necific, he did the work and went off. He did \nnot need to and therefore did=\r\n not become a Siddha. I see zero confusion here. \n\n=C2=A0 \nAdded to this th=\r\ne fact that Vivekananda was very clear, just as all the \ndisciples of Ramak=\r\nrshna were clear, that Ramakrishna was a special spiritual \nbeing, and high=\r\ner than them. Here too I see no confusion. \n\n=C2=A0 \n&lt;&lt;It is not necessary =\r\nthat there is a clear order of greatness. Infinity is \nneither greater than=\r\n nor less than nor equal to infinity.&gt;. \n\n=C2=A0 \nThis is what I call appro=\r\nximation. For an ordinary man, all saints maybe equally \nelevated. For Yogi=\r\ns, there maybe subtle differences and depths. The truth lies \nin the nuance=\r\ns. Anyway, Vivekananda&#39;s own words are more reliable for me than \nyours on =\r\nthis matter. And my previous explanation actually clarifies this \nstatement=\r\n of Sri Ramakrishna that Vivekananda was the &quot;ancient Rishis Nara&quot; who \ncam=\r\ne down for the good of mankind. \n\n=C2=A0 \n&lt;&lt;Wise men tread cautiously and d=\r\no not rush to judgment on others.&gt;&gt; \n=C2=A0 \nI am merely quoting and puttin=\r\ng together the analysis, statements of spiritually \ngreat people. It is not=\r\n as complex as you think! Saying that A is fatter than B, \nbased one statem=\r\nents and quotes from people who maybe in the know of things, is \nhardly a j=\r\nudgement. It could very well be a fact. \n\n=C2=A0 \n-Regards \n=C2=A0Rajarshi =\r\n\n=C2=A0 \nBazeecha-e-atfal hain duniya mere aage. \nHota hain shab-o-roz tama=\r\nsha mere aage \n=C2=A0 \nEk khel hain aur